This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, i) To investigate the efficacy and tolerability of benzodiazepines in panic disorder with or without agoraphobia, when compared with placebo or other forms of treatment, ii) More specifically we will aim to test the following hypotheses:, a) Benzodiazepines are more effective than placebo, b) Benzodiazepines are as effective in treating symptoms of panic disorder as TCAs,SSRIs, MAOIs or psychosocial interventions, c) Benzodiazepines are better tolerated than TCAs, SSRIs, MAOIs, d) High potency benzodiazepines are more effective than other benzodiazepines, e) Benzodiazepines are faster acting than other drugs or psychotherapy, F) Benzodiazepines do not induce relapse or withdrawal symptoms upon discontinuation